## ⛔ RULE #2: NEVER AUTO-RUN TERMINAL COMMANDS

**NEVER run terminal commands automatically.**

When a command is needed, STOP and tell the user exactly:
> "Run this command: `<command>`"

Only execute if the user explicitly says "run it" or "execute it."

---

## ⛔ RULE #3: READ BEFORE WRITING — ALWAYS

Before writing any code:
1. Read ALL files that will be affected
2. Understand the root cause — never patch symptoms
3. Check: is this production-safe at scale?
4. Check: does this break any existing feature?
5. Check: does this introduce a compliance risk (Visa/MC/GDPR)?

**Never use `as any`.** Use proper types or `unknown` with type guards.

---

## ⛔ RULE #4: EDGE CASES ARE NOT OPTIONAL

Every feature must handle:

| Scenario | What to do |
|---|---|
| DB call fails | try/catch, return structured error, never 500 the request |
| Webhook fires twice (duplicate) | Prisma upsert, idempotency key check |
| Stripe returns unexpected shape | Zod validation, log and skip |
| Email provider is down | Fire-and-forget with `.catch()` — never block retry engine |
| Card fingerprint missing | Skip Visa guard, log warning, do not crash |
| User connects from EU country | Set `retentionDays = 540`, not 90 |
| Hard decline code received | Never retry — `status = abandoned` immediately |
| Cron runs in dev without secret | Allow through. In prod: `assertCronSecret()` blocks it |
| Retry window expired (30d) | `status = abandoned`, do not attempt retry |
| Visa card-fingerprint >= 15/30d | Skip retry for that card, log compliance block |

