## ⛔ RULE #7: COMPLIANCE IS LOAD-BEARING CODE

These are not "nice to haves" — violations cause Stripe account bans and GDPR fines.

| Rule | Enforcement |
|---|---|
| Visa: max 15 retries per card fingerprint per 30 days | `retry-engine.ts` guard — hard stop |
| Mastercard: max 10 retries per card per 24 hours | `retry-engine.ts` guard — hard stop |
| Hard decline codes (03,04,07,12,57,62) | Never retry — immediate abandon |
| Retry window: 30 days max | Check `retryWindowEnd` before every attempt |
| GDPR EU retention: 540 days | Set on every `events_raw` insert |
| GDPR US retention: 90 days | Set on every `events_raw` insert |
| GDPR purge cron | Must run nightly — verify it's in `vercel.json` |

